<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,405,432]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Description.</emphasis>
A moderate-sized species, 
<typeStatus box="[645,743,405,431]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">holotype</typeStatus>
incomplete, 
<quantity box="[887,965,405,432]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="23.0">23 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[1074,1138,405,432]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
wide for 63 setigers; some 
<typeStatus box="[151,258,442,468]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratypes</typeStatus>
complete, up to 
<quantity box="[444,522,441,468]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[632,717,441,468]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
wide for approximately 90 setigers. Body elongate, with narrow crowded segments throughout (
<figureCitation box="[508,585,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
A–B, 4A–C); thoracic and 1–2 transitional segments about six times wider than long; middle and posterior segments narrower, more crowded. Transition from thoracic to abdominal segments marked by development of three annular rings ventral to neuropodia, consisting initially of a broad medial ring joined on subsequent segments by two thin lateral intersegmental rings (
<figureCitation box="[960,1027,585,611]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
B–C), thus providing ventral surface of each abdominal segment with three rings and an intersegmental groove between each segment. These rings most prominent in middle body segments (
<figureCitation box="[580,670,657,683]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
), becoming shallower and less evident in posterior segments. Both dorsal and ventral surfaces smooth, lacking longitudinal grooves or ridges. Some 
<typeStatus box="[1087,1194,694,720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">paratypes</typeStatus>
mature females with large irregularly shaped eggs, ranging from 
<quantity box="[643,786,729,756]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="mm" value="320.0" valueMax="350.0" valueMin="290.0">290–350 µm</quantity>
in diameter. Color in alcohol: opaque white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Prostomium triangular, short (
<figureCitation box="[537,630,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[643,681,765,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">4A</figureCitation>
), with nuchal organs elongate slits on posterior lateral margin (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), eyespots absent. Peristomium with one or two annular rings, first longer and narrower than second when two present (
<figureCitation box="[247,347,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[359,397,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">4A</figureCitation>
); presence of one or two peristomial rings not size related. Thorax with ten setigers followed by 1–2 transitional setigers (
<figureCitation box="[464,551,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
); boundary between last thoracic setiger and first abdominal demarcated by loss of most neurosetae and increase in size of neuropodial lobe on setigers 11–12 (
<figureCitation box="[1033,1122,909,935]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="11.[151,249,1420,1445]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,182,1394]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1436,181,1394]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 4. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564):A, anterior end, left lateral view; B, posterior thoracic and anterior abdominal setigers, left lateral view, setigers numbered; C, middle abdominal setigers, left lateral view, arrows denote tri-annular rings on venter. Paratype (MCZ 153565): D, posterior abdominal setiger, anterior view. Stained with Shirlastain A." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634278" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634278/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Thoracic notopodial and neuropodial lobes elongate with triangular base, both similar in form (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1378,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); abdominal notopodia becoming narrower, more elongate, shifting dorsally in position (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1189,981,1007]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D–E, 4D); abdominal neuropodia thickened, with two terminal lobes (
<figureCitation box="[688,764,1017,1043]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D–E, 4D); subpodial flanges and papillae absent. Branchiae first present from setiger 14–16 as rudiments; gradually increasing in size over middle abdominal segments, becoming broad and flattened, about one-third longer than notopodial lobe (
<figureCitation box="[927,1002,1089,1115]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs. 3</figureCitation>
D–E, 4D).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
All notosetae camerated capillaries; thoracic notosetae arranged in a tight fascicle with capillaries appearing to arise from a spiral, numbering about 30–40 per fascicle; abdominal capillaries numbering 15–20 per notopodium in anterior and middle setigers, reduced to 
<quantity box="[630,729,1197,1223]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" metricValueMax="4.572" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="in" value="14.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="10.0">10–18 in</quantity>
posterior setigers. Thoracic neurosetae all capillaries, with one prominent anterior row and 2–3 poorly organized secondary rows, numbering about 25–30 fascicle; abdominal neurosetae include 2–5 capillaries and 1–3 narrow aciculae with tips emergent, each short, smooth with rounded tip; furcate and flail setae absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" box="[199,963,1341,1368]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Pygidium bluntly rounded, bearing two thin elongate cirri (
<figureCitation box="[862,949,1341,1367]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1945,1970]" captionTargetBox="[202,1375,189,1913]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[196,1391,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Leitoscoloplos gordaensis n. sp. Holotype (MCZ 153564): A, anterior end, dorsal view. Paratype (MCZ 153565): B, posterior end, dorsal view; C, thoracic setiger, anterior view; D, anterior abdominal setiger, posterior view; E, posterior abdominal setiger, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3634276" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3634276/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1377,1404]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Variability</emphasis>
. The separation of the two peristomial rings is sometimes apparent only laterally, with the groove not crossing the dorsum. The anal cirri are usually lost, best observed on smaller specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" box="[199,829,1449,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,431,1449,1476]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Methyl Green stain</emphasis>
. No pattern, body stains uniformly.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1486,1512]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2020" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2020" box="[322,614,1485,1511]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gordaensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[322,614,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Leitoscoloplos gordaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[621,683,1486,1512]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[621,683,1486,1512]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="McIntosh" baseAuthorityYear="1885" box="[854,1022,1485,1511]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="kerguelensis">
<emphasis box="[854,1022,1485,1511]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. kerguelensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group in having branchiae first present from anterior abdominal setigers (
<bibRefCitation author="Blake, J. A." box="[571,706,1521,1547]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" pagination="1 - 145" refId="ref35753" refString="Blake, J. A. (2017) Polychaeta Orbiniidae from Antarctica, the Southern Ocean, the abyssal Pacific Ocean, and off South Amer- ica. Zootaxa, 4218 (1), 1 - 145. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4218.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">Blake 2017</bibRefCitation>
). The five species in this group from the eastern North Pacific are separated from the others in the key above and by additional characteristics in 
<tableCitation box="[1026,1110,1557,1583]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="51.[146,234,475,501]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison of 13 Species of Leitoscoloplos from deep-sea habitats greater than 750 m." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/A9A9ECA0964D2331D8C5FE77FB19FE67" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" tableUuid="A9A9ECA0964D2331D8C5FE77FB19FE67">Table 1</tableCitation>
. Of the four species that lack furcate setae, 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2020" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2020" box="[307,458,1593,1619]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gordaensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[307,458,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. gordaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[466,529,1594,1620]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[466,529,1594,1620]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2020" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2020" box="[584,696,1593,1619]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lunulus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[584,696,1593,1619]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. lunulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[704,767,1594,1620]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,767,1594,1620]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
each have a relatively short pre-setal region where the prostomium and peristomium are separated from one another by a distinct groove. The two species differ significantly from one another in that 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2020" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2020" box="[424,535,1665,1691]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="lunulus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[424,535,1665,1691]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. lunulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[542,603,1666,1692]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[542,603,1666,1692]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has a ventral cirrus and subpodial flange on the abdominal neuropodia that are lacking in 
<taxonomicName authority="Blake, 2020" authorityName="Blake" authorityYear="2020" box="[311,462,1701,1727]" class="Polychaeta" family="Orbiniidae" genus="Leitoscoloplos" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="gordaensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[311,462,1701,1727]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">L. gordaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[469,532,1702,1728]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[469,532,1702,1728]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1018,1737,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" box="[199,1018,1737,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,1738,1764]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species is named for its occurrence on the Gorda Ridge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,297,1836]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1773,1800]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Distribution</emphasis>
. Eastern Pacific, off northern 
<collectingRegion box="[679,793,1773,1799]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">California</collectingRegion>
in the vicinity of hydrothermal vents on the Gorda Ridge, Escanaba Trough, 
<quantity box="[359,447,1809,1836]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.271" pageId="9" pageNumber="10" unit="m" value="3271.0">3271 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
